SENATE BILL DRS35438-LRa-166
Short Title: Consumer Privacy Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Salvador (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROTECT CONSUMERS BY ENACTING THE CONSUMER PRIVACY ACT
3 OF NORTH CAROLINA AND TO APPROPRIATE FUNDS FOR THAT PURPOSE.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. This act shall be known and may be cited as the "North Carolina
6 Consumer Privacy Act."
7 SECTION 2. The General Statutes are amended by adding a new Chapter to read:
8 "Chapter 75F.
9 "Consumer Privacy Act.
10 "§ 75F-1. Definitions.
11 (a) This Chapter shall be known and may be cited as the "North Carolina Consumer
12 Privacy Act."
13 (b) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this Chapter:
14 (1) Account. – The Consumer Privacy Account established in G.S. 75F-14.
15 (2) Affiliate. – An entity that (i) controls, is controlled by, or is under common
16 control with another entity or (ii) shares common branding with another entity.
17 (3) Aggregated data. – Information that relates to a group or category of
18 consumers (i) from which individual consumer identities have been removed
19 and (ii) that is not linked or reasonably linkable to any consumer.
20 (4) Air carrier. – As defined in 49 U.S.C. § 40102.
21 (5) Authenticate. – To use reasonable means to determine that a consumer's
22 request to exercise the rights described in G.S. 75F-4 is made by the consumer
23 who is entitled to exercise those rights.
24 (6) Biometric data. – Data generated by automatic measurements of an
25 individual's unique biological characteristics. The term includes an
26 individual's fingerprint, voiceprint, eye retinas, irises, or any other unique
27 biological pattern or characteristic that is used to identify a specific individual.
28 Biometric data does not include any of the following:
29 a. A physical or digital photograph.
30 b. A video or audio recording.
31 c. Data generated from an item described in sub-subdivision a. or b. of
32 this subdivision.
33 d. Information captured from a patient in a health care setting.
34 e. Information collected, used, or stored for treatment, payment, or health
35 care operations as those terms are defined in 45 C.F.R. Parts 160, 162,
36 and 164.
*DRS35438-LRa-166*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (7) Business associate. – As defined in 45 C.F.R. § 160.103.
2 (8) Child. – An individual younger than 13 years old.
3 (9) Consent. – An affirmative act by a consumer that unambiguously indicates the
4 consumer's voluntary and informed agreement to allow a person to process
5 personal data related to the consumer.
6 (10) Consumer. – An individual who is a resident of this State acting in an
7 individual or household context. The term does not include an individual
8 acting in a commercial or employment context.
9 (11) Control or controlled. – Includes each of the following: (i) ownership of, or
10 the power to vote, more than fifty percent (50%) of the outstanding shares of
11 any class of voting securities of an entity; (ii) control in any manner over the
12 election of a majority of the directors or of the individuals exercising similar
13 functions; and (iii) the power to exercise controlling influence of the
14 management of an entity.
15 (12) Controller. – A person doing business in this State who determines the
16 purposes for which, and the means by which, personal data are processed,
17 regardless of whether the person makes the determination alone or with others
18 that, alone or jointly with others, determines the purpose and means of
19 processing personal data.
20 (13) Covered entity. – As defined in 45 C.F.R. § 160.103.
21 (14) De-identified data. – Data that cannot reasonably be linked to an identified or
22 identifiable individual that are possessed by a controller who does all of the
23 following:
24 a. Takes reasonable measures to ensure that a person cannot associate the
25 data with an individual.
26 b. Publicly commits to maintain and use the data only in de-identified
27 form and not attempt to reidentify the data.
28 c. Contractually obligates any recipients of the data to comply with the
29 requirements described in sub-subdivisions a. and b. of this
30 subdivision.
31 (15) Director. – The Director of the Division.
32 (16) Division. – The Consumer Protection Division of the North Carolina
33 Department of Justice or other unit of the Department of Justice engaging in
34 activities under this Chapter.
35 (17) Government entity. – The State or any local political subdivision of the State.
36 (18) Health care facility. – Any entity licensed pursuant to Chapter 122C, 131D,
37 or 131E of the General Statutes or Article 64 of Chapter 58 of the General
38 Statutes and any clinical laboratory certified under the federal Clinical
39 Laboratory Improvement Amendments in section 353 of the Public Health
40 Service Act (42 U.S.C. § 263a).
41 (19) Health care provider. – Includes:
42 a. An individual who is licensed, certified, or otherwise authorized under
43 Chapter 90 or 90B of the General Statutes to provide health care
44 services in the ordinary course of business or practice of a profession
45 or in an approved education or training program.
46 b. A health care facility where health care services are provided to
47 patients, residents, or others to whom such services are provided as
48 allowed by law.
49 c. Individuals licensed under Chapter 90 of the General Statutes or
50 practicing under a waiver in accordance with G.S. 90-12.5.
