1 d. Any emergency medical services personnel as defined in
2 G.S. 131E-155(7).
3 e. Any individual who is employed as a health care facility administrator,
4 executive, supervisor, board member, trustee, or other person in a
5 managerial position or comparable role at a health care facility.
6 f. An agent or employee of a health care facility that is licensed, certified,
7 or otherwise authorized to provide health care services.
8 g. An officer or director of a health care facility.
9 h. An agent or employee of a health care provider who is licensed,
10 certified, or otherwise authorized to provide health care services.
11 (20) Identifiable individual. – An individual who can be readily identified, directly
12 or indirectly.
13 (21) Institution of higher education. – A public or private institution of higher
14 education.
15 (22) Local political subdivision. – Includes a city, a county, a local school
16 administrative unit as defined in G.S. 115C-5, or a community college.
17 (23) Nonprofit organization. – Any corporation exempt from taxation under
18 section 501(c)(3), 501(c)(6), or 501(c)(12) of the Internal Revenue Code.
19 (24) Personal data. – Information that can be used to distinguish or trace an
20 individual's identity, either alone or when combined with other information.
21 The term does not include information that is a public record under Chapter
22 132 of the General Statutes or information made available to the general
23 public lawfully and intentionally.
24 (25) Process. – Any operation or set of operations performed on personal data,
25 including collection, use, storage, disclosure, analysis, deletion, or
26 modification of personal data.
27 (26) Processor. – A person who processes personal data on behalf of a controller.
28 (27) Protected health information. – As defined in 45 C.F.R. § 160.103.
29 (28) Pseudonymous data. – Personal data that cannot be attributed to a specific
30 individual without the use of additional information, if the additional
31 information is (i) kept separately from the consumer's personal data and (ii)
32 subject to appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure that the
33 personal data is not attributable to an identified or identifiable individual.
34 (29) Publicly available information. – Information that a person (i) lawfully obtains
35 from a record of a governmental entity, (ii) reasonably believes a consumer or
36 widely distributed media has lawfully made available to the general public, or
37 (iii) if the consumer has not restricted the information to a specific audience,
38 obtains from a person to whom the consumer disclosed the information.
39 (30) Right. – A consumer right described in G.S. 75F-4.
40 (31) Sale, sell, or sold. – The exchange of personal data for monetary consideration
41 by the controller to a third party. The terms do not include any of the
42 following:
43 a. A controller's disclosure of personal data to a processor who processes
44 the personal data on behalf of the controller.
45 b. A controller's disclosure of personal data to an affiliate of the
46 controller.
47 c. Considering the context in which the consumer provided the personal
48 data to the controller, a controller's disclosure of personal data to a
49 third party if the purpose is consistent with a consumer's reasonable
50 expectations.
