14 (32) Sensitive data. – Personal data that reveals any of the following:
15 a. An individual's (i) racial or ethnic origin, (ii) religious beliefs, (iii)
16 sexual orientation, (iv) citizenship or immigration status, or (v)
17 information regarding an individual's medical history, mental or
18 physical health condition, or medical treatment or diagnosis by a
19 health care professional. The term does not include personal data that
20 reveals an individual's racial or ethnic origin if the personal data are
21 processed by a video communication service. If the personal data are
22 processed by a person licensed to provide health care under State or
23 federal law, information regarding an individual's medical history,
24 mental or physical health condition, or medical treatment or diagnosis
25 by a health care professional, then the personal data is not sensitive
26 data.
27 b. The processing of genetic or biometric data if the processing is for the
28 purpose of identifying a specific individual.
29 c. Specific geolocation data.
30 (33) Specific geological location. – Information derived from technology,
31 including global positioning system level latitude and longitude coordinates,
32 that directly identifies an individual's specific location, accurate within a
33 radius of 1,750 feet or less. The term does not include (i) the content of a
34 communication or (ii) any data generated by or connected to advanced utility
35 metering infrastructure systems or equipment used by a utility.
36 (34) Targeted advertising. – Displaying an advertisement to a consumer where the
37 consumer is selected based upon personal data obtained from the consumer's
38 activities over time and across nonaffiliated websites or online applications to
39 predict the consumer's preferences and interests. The term does not include
40 any advertising:
41 a. Based upon a consumer's activities within the controller's website or
42 online application or any affiliated website or online application.
43 b. Based on the context of a consumer's current search query or visit to a
44 website or online application.
45 c. Directed to a consumer in response to the consumer's request for
46 information, a product, a service, or feedback.
47 d. Processing personal data solely to measure or report advertising
48 performance, reach, or frequency.
49 (35) Third party. – A person other than the consumer, controller, or processor or
50 an affiliate or contractor of the controller or processor.
