7 information's secrecy.
8 "§ 75F-2. Applicability.
9 (a) This Chapter applies to any controller or processor who:
10 (1) Conducts business in this State or produces a product or service that is targeted
11 to consumers who are residents of this State;
12 (2) Has annual revenue of twenty-five million dollars ($25,000,000) or more; and
13 (3) Satisfies one or more of the following thresholds:
14 a. During a calendar year, controls or processes personal data of 100,000
15 or more consumers; or
16 b. Derives over fifty percent (50%) of the entity's gross revenue from the
17 sale of personal data and controls or processes personal data of 25,000
18 or more consumers.
19 (b) This Chapter does not apply to any of the following:
20 (1) A governmental entity or a third party under contract with a governmental
21 entity when the third party is acting on behalf of the governmental entity.
22 (2) A tribe.
23 (3) An institution of higher education.
24 (4) A nonprofit corporation.
25 (5) A covered entity.
26 (6) A business associate.
27 (7) Information that meets the definition of one of the following:
28 a. Protected health information for purposes of the federal Health
29 Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996, 42 U.S.C. §
30 1320d et seq., and related regulations.
31 b. Patient identifying information for purposes of 42 C.F.R. Part 2.
32 c. Identifiable private information for purposes of the federal Policy for
33 the Protection of Human Subjects, 45 C.F.R. Part 46.
34 d. Identifiable private information or personal data collected as part of
35 human subjects research pursuant to or under the same standards as:
36 1. The good clinical practice guidelines issued by the
37 International Council for Harmonisation; or
38 2. The Protection of Human Subjects under 21 C.F.R. Part 50 and
39 Institutional Review Boards under 21 C.F.R. Part 56.
40 e. Personal data used or shared in research conducted in accordance with
41 one or more of the requirements described in sub-subdivision b. of this
42 subdivision.
43 f. Information and documents created for purposes of the federal Health
44 Care Quality Improvement Act of 1986, 42 U.S.C. § 11101 et seq., and
45 related regulations.
46 g. Patient safety work product for purposes of 42 C.F.R. Part 3.
47 h. Information that is:
48 1. De-identified in accordance with the requirements for
49 de-identification set forth in 45 C.F.R. Part 164; and
50 2. Derived from any of the health care-related information listed
51 above in this subdivision.
